          "en": "Use when reasoning about composition and stability through the chemical-elements matrix — everything is made of atoms, and the periodic table adds a chemistry to the logic: each atom has a VALENCE (electrons it shares to fill its shell), stability is the OCTET (a full outer shell — the noble gases), and atoms BOND to reach it. The new perspective: the erpax corpus is a MOLECULE — an atom's valence is its open links, and the corpus is stable exactly when aura gap = 0 (all shells full)."
